During a high-level panel discussion earlier on Wednesday, emphasis was made by the panellists for African governments to take away financial risk, regarding misappropriation of funds. Countries have given each other 10 years to restore the biodiversity in Africa amid the devastating effects of climate change. It’s no longer business as usual, with only one generation left to conserve protected areas. --John Cassim/Channel Africa-- Minister of State for Economic Planning in Rwanda, Cluadine Uwera speaking during a panel discussion on “Investing in Biodiversity and diversifying in financing models” Credit: John Cassim #ChannelAfrica pic.twitter.com/YTHIdYXiTh